Etymology[edit]

Literally "to feed crows on a cross".

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /in ˈkru.ke ˈkor.woːs ˈpaːs.koː/, [ɪn̪ ˈkrʊ.kɛ ˈkɔr.woːs ˈpaːs.koː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /in ˈkru.t͡ʃe ˈkor.vos ˈpas.ko/, [in ˈkruː.t͡ʃɛ ˈkɔr.vɔs ˈpas.kɔ]

Verb[edit]

in cruce corvōs pāscō (present infinitive in cruce corvōs pāscere, perfect active in cruce corvōs pāvī, supine in cruce corvōs pāstum); third conjugation

  1. to be hanged
